1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,912
=Episode 24=
(Spring Breeze Brushes Your Face)

3
00:01:38,130 --> 00:01:38,850
No.

4
00:01:38,850 --> 00:01:39,731
I've got things to do.

5
00:01:42,290 --> 00:01:44,731
Come clean. Are you dating someone?

6
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:45,811
Are you?

7
00:01:46,050 --> 00:01:47,330
- Are you?
- Are you?

8
00:01:47,410 --> 00:01:48,171
No, I'm not.

9
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:50,490
Come on, stop it.

10
00:01:51,611 --> 00:01:53,130
Stop it.

11
00:01:54,330 --> 00:01:55,731
We saw you two.

12
00:01:55,770 --> 00:01:56,891
Exactly.

13
00:01:57,731 --> 00:01:58,811
He came to see...

14
00:01:59,451 --> 00:02:00,651
He came to see us.

15
00:02:01,171 --> 00:02:02,690
Why are you so nervous?

16
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:07,091
It's you
who doesn't want it public, or him?

17
00:02:10,051 --> 00:02:10,971
It's me.

18
00:02:11,890 --> 00:02:13,931
I was too embarrassed to tell you.

19
00:02:14,251 --> 00:02:15,971
Why would you be embarrassed?

20
00:02:16,170 --> 00:02:18,491
Are you afraid
we'll think you're showing off?

21
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:21,091
What's there to show off?

22
00:02:21,570 --> 00:02:24,331
Oh my god,
Mr. Liu isn't worth bragging about?

23
00:02:24,610 --> 00:02:26,931
Over half the girls
in his class admire him.

24
00:02:27,051 --> 00:02:28,290
His dorm was piled with gifts

25
00:02:28,491 --> 00:02:29,730
on his birthday.

26
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:31,251
It's not Mr. Liu.

27
00:02:31,771 --> 00:02:34,730
We're just working on a project.
What are you thinking?

28
00:02:35,491 --> 00:02:37,331
We can tell from how you're acting.

29
00:02:37,570 --> 00:02:40,010
If you're not dating anyone,
I'll eat every bed in this room.

30
00:02:40,890 --> 00:02:43,450
You don't even tell your roommates.

31
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,331
That's so cold.

32
00:02:47,051 --> 00:02:47,651
That's right.

33
00:02:48,531 --> 00:02:50,211
My boyfriend came from my hometown.

34
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:52,491
Boyfriend?

35
00:02:52,491 --> 00:02:53,251
Really?

36
00:02:53,811 --> 00:02:54,570
Who is he?

37
00:02:54,931 --> 00:02:56,570
That boyfriend you called?

38
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:01,931
What?

39
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:02,971
That's great.

40
00:03:02,971 --> 00:03:04,248
You're finally dating someone.

41
00:03:04,610 --> 00:03:05,130
(Zhihua Night Market)
Want some?

42
00:03:05,410 --> 00:03:06,130
- Want this?
- All starch.

43
00:03:06,130 --> 00:03:06,690
Not tasty.

44
00:03:07,331 --> 00:03:08,331
You're sneaking around,

45
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,290
dating someone without telling us.

46
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:11,450
- Yeah.
- You must

47
00:03:11,931 --> 00:03:12,651
treat us to...

48
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:13,211
- Ice cream.
- Yeah.

49
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:14,531
Oh my.

50
00:03:14,531 --> 00:03:15,450
Among all these foods,

51
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:17,410
you only want ice cream? Aim higher.

52
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:19,290
Pick whatever you want.

53
00:03:19,290 --> 00:03:20,211
- My treat.
- Really?

54
00:03:20,211 --> 00:03:22,331
- Yeah.
- He came to Qingzhou for you?

55
00:03:22,331 --> 00:03:23,690
That's so romantic.

56
00:03:25,771 --> 00:03:27,771
Is he here to study or work?

57
00:03:28,010 --> 00:03:28,771
He's working.

58
00:03:30,010 --> 00:03:31,251
Where is he working?

59
00:03:32,472 --> 00:03:33,651
At a state-owned enterprise.

60
00:03:34,730 --> 00:03:35,410
Really?

61
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:36,811
That's impressive.

62
00:03:37,251 --> 00:03:38,651
That's really hard to get into.

63
00:03:39,371 --> 00:03:41,290
His family has good connections?

64
00:03:41,290 --> 00:03:42,890
How would I know?

65
00:03:42,890 --> 00:03:44,850
I'm too embarrassed to ask.
How can I ask that?

66
00:03:45,410 --> 00:03:46,290
How much is this?

67
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:47,091
Twelve per serving.

68
00:03:47,290 --> 00:03:48,450
Twelve. Want some?

69
00:03:48,890 --> 00:03:50,091
It's got hair on it.

70
00:03:52,610 --> 00:03:53,811
So where is he staying?

71
00:03:55,971 --> 00:03:58,651
His relative has an empty place

72
00:03:58,771 --> 00:04:00,170
and lets him stay.

73
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:04,410
But he can't live
at a relative's place forever.

74
00:04:04,771 --> 00:04:05,450
Yeah.

75
00:04:05,570 --> 00:04:07,211
We'll buy a place here in a few years.

76
00:04:07,610 --> 00:04:08,570
That looks good.

77
00:04:08,890 --> 00:04:09,491
Thanks.

78
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:11,610
How much is it?

79
00:04:11,610 --> 00:04:12,890
The cumin one looks okay.

80
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:18,651
There's... a hot pot place over there.

81
00:04:19,451 --> 00:04:20,410
Let's go eat there.

82
00:04:20,451 --> 00:04:21,410
I know that place.

83
00:04:24,211 --> 00:04:25,410
Okay, go in first.

84
00:04:25,410 --> 00:04:26,691
I'll buy something else.

85
00:04:26,691 --> 00:04:27,691
Get something pricy.

86
00:04:47,026 --> 00:04:48,610
(2023, Qingzhou)

87
00:04:48,610 --> 00:04:49,490
Ren Xiaoming.

88
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:51,211
When the judge asks
about the third party,

89
00:04:51,211 --> 00:04:52,651
how are you going to answer?

90
00:04:57,810 --> 00:04:58,971
We're almost there.

91
00:05:06,571 --> 00:05:07,651
Ren Xiaoming is here.

92
00:05:08,730 --> 00:05:10,571
We heard about your love affair.

93
00:05:10,571 --> 00:05:11,490
It's Ren Xiaoming.

94
00:05:12,691 --> 00:05:13,490
Check out the video.

95
00:05:13,571 --> 00:05:14,651
Who posted it online?

96
00:05:14,651 --> 00:05:16,290
Mr. Liu, look.

97
00:05:23,730 --> 00:05:24,850
Can you tell us

98
00:05:24,850 --> 00:05:25,930
if it's real?

99
00:05:29,891 --> 00:05:30,891
I'm not crazy.

100
00:05:30,891 --> 00:05:31,651
Stop filming.

101
00:05:31,730 --> 00:05:32,331
Don't hide.

102
00:05:32,651 --> 00:05:33,370
I'm not crazy.

103
00:05:33,370 --> 00:05:34,331
Stop filming.

104
00:05:34,571 --> 00:05:35,331
She lost it.

105
00:05:39,930 --> 00:05:40,730
Was it you?

106
00:05:40,930 --> 00:05:41,651
Xiaoming.

107
00:05:41,971 --> 00:05:43,331
- Was it you?
- Hurry, go.

108
00:05:43,490 --> 00:05:44,011
Ren Xiaoming.

109
00:05:44,091 --> 00:05:44,891
Step aside.

110
00:05:54,610 --> 00:05:59,186
(Counseling Room)

111
00:06:20,011 --> 00:06:21,651
Her brother has a mental illness.

112
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:24,370
She saw a psychologist
for depression while in the US.

113
00:06:24,571 --> 00:06:27,730
The US assessment can only serve
as a reference for us.

114
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:33,720
(Psych Evaluation)

115
00:06:38,322 --> 00:06:40,882
(Counseling Room)

116
00:07:05,331 --> 00:07:05,930
Ms. Liang.

117
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:06,930
How is it?

118
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:08,771
Her assessment results are out.

119
00:07:09,091 --> 00:07:10,771
Based on her drawing,

120
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:13,531
her psychosis score is quite high.

121
00:07:14,651 --> 00:07:15,651
Psychosis?

122
00:07:16,091 --> 00:07:19,370
Relax. It doesn't necessarily mean
a psychiatric disorder.

123
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:22,571
Let's look at her scale test.

124
00:07:22,930 --> 00:07:24,250
Look at this scale.

125
00:07:24,331 --> 00:07:26,410
The answers are too normal.

126
00:07:26,730 --> 00:07:28,370
More normal than normal.

127
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:31,531
Now look at this drawing of hers.

128
00:07:31,971 --> 00:07:33,170
The contrast is too stark.

129
00:07:33,691 --> 00:07:35,531
It seems like she's hiding something.

130
00:07:35,771 --> 00:07:36,691
What does that mean?

131
00:07:36,771 --> 00:07:37,531
It means

132
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:41,370
she's either a seasoned psychologist

133
00:07:41,571 --> 00:07:45,211
or she's a patient
currently experiencing symptoms.

134
00:07:46,971 --> 00:07:47,730
So what do we do?

135
00:07:48,331 --> 00:07:50,290
I recommend hospitalization

136
00:07:50,531 --> 00:07:54,771
for further observation, evaluation,
diagnosis, and then treatment.

137
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:05,050
Did you forge Ren Xiaoming's
psychiatric records from the US?

138
00:08:07,730 --> 00:08:09,930
That part is true.

139
00:08:11,011 --> 00:08:13,370
She was unstable
when she first arrived in the US,

140
00:08:13,930 --> 00:08:16,610
having nightmares,
crying, and screaming.

141
00:08:17,651 --> 00:08:20,850
The video was clearly edited.
Was that you?

142
00:08:21,091 --> 00:08:23,050
I did edit this video.

143
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:25,211
I did it and wanted to submit it

144
00:08:25,331 --> 00:08:28,250
to the judge as confidential evidence
during the court trial.

145
00:08:28,370 --> 00:08:31,011
My original intention
was to fight against the divorce.

146
00:08:32,091 --> 00:08:34,451
Think about it.
For a public divorce lawsuit

147
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:37,211
in front of so many people,

148
00:08:37,451 --> 00:08:39,250
making it ugly is the worst thing.

149
00:08:39,411 --> 00:08:40,931
Don't you think I understand that?

150
00:08:42,850 --> 00:08:44,010
So you're saying

151
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:46,890
that Ren Xiaoming posted it online?

152
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:50,490
With divorce,
I'd at most suffer financial loss.

153
00:08:51,051 --> 00:08:53,850
Posting it would ruin my public image.

154
00:08:53,850 --> 00:08:55,691
So why would she ruin her public image?

155
00:08:56,010 --> 00:08:57,610
She's getting back at me.

156
00:08:57,931 --> 00:08:59,571
I tricked her in the copyright case.

157
00:09:00,171 --> 00:09:04,451
She planned this from the start,
skipping court to draw media attention.

158
00:09:04,931 --> 00:09:07,051
She just wants to destroy me over this.

159
00:09:07,451 --> 00:09:08,530
Nothing you say matters.

160
00:09:08,730 --> 00:09:11,530
I only believe
what Ren Xiaoming tells me herself.

161
00:09:11,811 --> 00:09:13,331
You think she wouldn't lie to you?

162
00:09:13,730 --> 00:09:15,291
She could've won the copyright case.

163
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:17,490
But she hid
the most crucial evidence from you.

164
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:19,931
That's why you lost, you fool.

165
00:09:20,331 --> 00:09:22,291
She tricked and deceived you.

166
00:09:26,811 --> 00:09:28,730
What evidence?

167
00:09:33,411 --> 00:09:35,730
Ms. Liang, the case isn't over yet.

168
00:09:35,931 --> 00:09:40,370
Is it professional for you
to ask me so many questions in private?

169
00:09:43,691 --> 00:09:44,650
You piece of trash.

170
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:53,770
You...

171
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:57,010
Why are you giving me a hard time?

172
00:09:58,490 --> 00:09:59,890
Let's sort things out.

173
00:10:03,730 --> 00:10:07,211
Ren Xiaoming achieved two goals

174
00:10:08,130 --> 00:10:10,051
through two lawsuits.

175
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:12,650
In the copyright case,

176
00:10:12,971 --> 00:10:15,650
Liu Xiaoran's court testimony
denied the diary's existence.

177
00:10:16,890 --> 00:10:17,650
The divorce case.

178
00:10:20,530 --> 00:10:22,171
Thanks to the media attention,

179
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:25,530
the fact that she had a history
of mental illness

180
00:10:25,730 --> 00:10:26,584
and that her brother

181
00:10:27,448 --> 00:10:31,051
is a hereditary mental patient
was widely spread.

182
00:10:53,432 --> 00:10:55,794
(Copyright Case, Diary
Divorce Case, Mental Illness)

183
00:10:55,794 --> 00:10:58,537
(Ren Xiaoming)

184
00:11:05,618 --> 00:11:08,571
(Police)

185
00:11:08,571 --> 00:11:11,171
Come on, everyone. Share your thoughts.

186
00:11:11,890 --> 00:11:14,490
She hid key evidence
in the copyright case.

187
00:11:14,691 --> 00:11:16,130
If she really is the murderer,

188
00:11:16,331 --> 00:11:19,091
once she is classified
as having a hereditary mental illness,

189
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:20,490
the capacity assessment phase

190
00:11:20,850 --> 00:11:24,171
of the trial will become
much more unpredictable.

191
00:11:24,451 --> 00:11:26,890
(Capacity)
She's trying to get off the hook.

192
00:11:27,931 --> 00:11:29,171
(Get off the hook)
Last month,

193
00:11:30,010 --> 00:11:31,211
Ren Xiaoming

194
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:34,451
bought two apartments in Qidaohezi's

195
00:11:34,811 --> 00:11:35,931
most expensive development.

196
00:11:36,411 --> 00:11:38,530
She also bought savings-type
commercial insurance

197
00:11:39,051 --> 00:11:42,010
for Ren Meiyan and Ren Xiaofei.

198
00:11:42,571 --> 00:11:45,291
It makes sense
if this is about transferring assets

199
00:11:45,530 --> 00:11:47,171
(Buying properties, insurance)
for divorce.

200
00:11:47,691 --> 00:11:50,051
She even spent money on the dead.

201
00:11:51,171 --> 00:11:53,650
She also bought a plot
at Wuming Mountain Cemetery.

202
00:11:54,291 --> 00:11:55,171
(Wuming Mountain Cemetery)
Wuming Mountain?

203
00:11:55,811 --> 00:11:59,130
It's over 40 kilometers from the city.

204
00:11:59,291 --> 00:12:00,331
That's so far away.

205
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:01,211
Yeah.

206
00:12:01,691 --> 00:12:03,250
Maybe she's avoiding Bai Shu.

207
00:12:04,171 --> 00:12:07,370
Ren Xiaoming tried to get off the hook
through these two cases.

208
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:11,691
She bought property and insurance
to transfer assets.

209
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:14,931
She even figured out where to be buried.

210
00:12:15,571 --> 00:12:18,571
So I speculate that she is the killer.

211
00:12:19,331 --> 00:12:20,850
Your speculation means nothing.

212
00:12:21,091 --> 00:12:23,770
Look at the time of the crime: 2010.

213
00:12:24,331 --> 00:12:27,571
You need to confirm
she was in Qidaohezi in 2010.

214
00:12:28,051 --> 00:12:29,211
Assuming

215
00:12:29,530 --> 00:12:32,770
the crime scene is the back hill
of Rest Cemetery, as we deduced,

216
00:12:32,931 --> 00:12:34,370
you have to confirm

217
00:12:34,610 --> 00:12:37,610
that she went to the back hill
of Rest Cemetery in 2010.

218
00:12:37,850 --> 00:12:40,010
Finally, the motive.

219
00:12:40,331 --> 00:12:42,650
We don't even know
if the deceased is Zhou Na.

220
00:12:42,850 --> 00:12:45,571
How can we determine
Ren Xiaoming's motive?

221
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:49,091
None of this nails Ren Xiaoming.

222
00:12:49,610 --> 00:12:51,971
We can't classify Ren Xiaoming

223
00:12:52,331 --> 00:12:54,010
as a suspect for now.

224
00:13:10,971 --> 00:13:13,010
Our home hasn't changed much.

225
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:14,850
Only the TV is new.

226
00:13:16,051 --> 00:13:17,411
It's still the same.

227
00:13:19,010 --> 00:13:21,091
This street and your home

228
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:23,691
seem to be frozen in time.

229
00:13:25,291 --> 00:13:26,931
Walking into this alley today

230
00:13:28,171 --> 00:13:29,490
felt like traveling through time.

231
00:13:31,451 --> 00:13:33,331
You speak so eloquently.

232
00:13:33,490 --> 00:13:34,850
I feel the same way,

233
00:13:34,850 --> 00:13:36,490
but I can't put it into words.

234
00:13:38,530 --> 00:13:39,530
It has changed, though.

235
00:13:41,890 --> 00:13:43,051
Many old neighbors

236
00:13:44,010 --> 00:13:46,530
on this street have moved away.

237
00:13:48,051 --> 00:13:50,130
They either went
to live with their children

238
00:13:50,171 --> 00:13:53,171
or moved into high-rises.
Many houses are rented out now.

239
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:54,811
A couple of years ago,

240
00:13:55,091 --> 00:13:57,211
Xiaoming wanted to buy a place,
but I didn't let her.

241
00:13:58,411 --> 00:14:01,291
She asked me to move to Qingzhou,
but I didn't want to go.

242
00:14:01,811 --> 00:14:03,770
People are really strange.

243
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:05,370
When I was young,

244
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:08,451
I desperately wanted
to leave this place.

245
00:14:09,091 --> 00:14:12,171
But now that I've aged,
I don't want to go anywhere.

246
00:14:13,571 --> 00:14:15,411
Ms. Ren, are you okay?

247
00:14:15,811 --> 00:14:18,171
It's fine. Just inflammation.

248
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,770
Let me take you
to the hospital for a checkup.

249
00:14:22,171 --> 00:14:23,931
No need. Throat inflammation.

250
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:28,890
As long as I'm here,
this place will stay like this.

251
00:14:31,010 --> 00:14:32,490
No matter how far you roam,

252
00:14:33,691 --> 00:14:35,010
you'll always have a home here.

253
00:14:39,010 --> 00:14:39,971
It's just a pity

254
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:44,091
that none of you want to come home.

255
00:14:50,130 --> 00:14:51,171
Sorry, Ms. Ren.

256
00:14:52,010 --> 00:14:53,291
It's okay.

257
00:14:53,971 --> 00:14:55,291
Kids never stay home.

258
00:14:56,931 --> 00:14:59,010
Xiaoming stayed in the US for years

259
00:14:59,971 --> 00:15:01,051
without coming home.

260
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,571
Sometimes, she only called once a year.

261
00:15:06,211 --> 00:15:08,490
It's part of growing up.

262
00:15:10,091 --> 00:15:11,091
When you

263
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:14,571
truly grow up, you'll want to come home.

264
00:15:19,171 --> 00:15:21,650
Actually, Xiaoming doesn't
want to come home

265
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:23,091
because of me.

266
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:28,331
She holds a grudge against me.

267
00:15:29,051 --> 00:15:29,850
What happened?

268
00:15:35,411 --> 00:15:36,650
He Yuqiong.

269
00:15:38,706 --> 00:15:41,944
(2008, Qingzhou)

270
00:15:52,650 --> 00:15:55,211
Didn't I teach you this yesterday?

271
00:15:55,770 --> 00:15:57,650
We covered it yesterday, right?

272
00:15:57,730 --> 00:15:58,370
Look.

273
00:15:59,051 --> 00:16:00,691
Thirty-six divided by four equals nine.

274
00:16:00,691 --> 00:16:02,610
I taught you this yesterday, right?

275
00:16:02,691 --> 00:16:04,130
Why did you write three?

276
00:16:04,850 --> 00:16:07,691
Mom, did you make braised pork?

277
00:16:08,931 --> 00:16:09,811
Just out of the pot.

278
00:16:10,091 --> 00:16:11,691
Let me have a piece?

279
00:16:12,850 --> 00:16:13,530
My boy.

280
00:16:15,650 --> 00:16:17,730
Just one bite. Study hard.

281
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:21,130
Mom, can you put it here?

282
00:16:21,451 --> 00:16:22,370
Sorry about that.

283
00:16:22,811 --> 00:16:24,091
This child just loves to eat.

284
00:16:24,091 --> 00:16:25,610
It's alright. Just leave it here.

285
00:16:25,770 --> 00:16:26,770
Study hard.

286
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:37,530
Is it good?

287
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:38,250
Yeah.

288
00:16:39,010 --> 00:16:39,931
How good is it?

289
00:16:40,211 --> 00:16:41,211
It's extremely good.

290
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:42,530
Extremely good?

291
00:16:42,610 --> 00:16:43,650
What's the taste?

292
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:45,610
Are you craving it too?

293
00:16:46,211 --> 00:16:47,890
Nonsense. Stay focused.

294
00:16:48,811 --> 00:16:51,811
Mom, get chopsticks.
My teacher wants some too.

295
00:16:52,291 --> 00:16:53,010
Okay.

296
00:16:53,010 --> 00:16:55,171
No need, ma'am. I wasn't...

297
00:16:55,171 --> 00:16:56,370
I kept some for you.

298
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:58,931
Just have some.

299
00:17:00,331 --> 00:17:01,370
Thank you.

300
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:02,091
No problem.

301
00:18:33,618 --> 00:18:36,856
(Emergency)

302
00:18:47,704 --> 00:18:48,713
(He Yuqiong)

303
00:18:55,218 --> 00:18:56,825
(Ren Xiaoming)

304
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:03,864
(He Yuqiong)

305
00:19:12,882 --> 00:19:14,776
(Phone Storage)

306
00:19:14,776 --> 00:19:18,072
(Ren Xiaoming)

307
00:19:34,936 --> 00:19:37,252
(Mom)

308
00:19:48,851 --> 00:19:49,851
Mom.

309
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:53,010
Stop calling. It's annoying.

310
00:19:53,010 --> 00:19:55,770
I'm dying.

311
00:20:08,691 --> 00:20:09,530
Ren Xiaoming.

312
00:20:10,090 --> 00:20:12,490
Ren Xiaoming.

313
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:14,851
Ren Xiaoming.

314
00:20:16,530 --> 00:20:17,211
Ren Xiaoming.

315
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:24,010
Ren Xiaoming.

316
00:20:25,570 --> 00:20:26,490
Are you okay?

317
00:20:29,171 --> 00:20:30,891
The nurse says you should be fine now.

318
00:20:32,211 --> 00:20:33,490
Go away.

319
00:20:34,050 --> 00:20:36,891
Sorry, I delivered goods
seven or eight times last night

320
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:39,371
and left my phone
at one of the delivery points.

321
00:20:39,691 --> 00:20:40,810
I went looking for it.

322
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:42,971
Then I found out the phone was dead.

323
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,810
I charged it and saw

324
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:46,010
all the missed phone calls.

325
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,090
I was so worried. Are you okay now?

326
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:50,371
The nurse said you're much better.

327
00:20:50,851 --> 00:20:52,851
Are you still hurting? Can I touch you?

328
00:20:52,851 --> 00:20:53,651
Leave me alone.

329
00:20:54,171 --> 00:20:55,411
I was wrong. I'm sorry.

330
00:20:55,851 --> 00:20:56,651
I'm so sorry.

331
00:20:57,010 --> 00:20:58,651
I messed up. I was so worried.

332
00:21:00,090 --> 00:21:03,490
I'm so sorry.

333
00:21:04,851 --> 00:21:05,691
I'm thirsty.

334
00:21:05,891 --> 00:21:08,050
Thirsty? I'll get you some water.

335
00:21:09,131 --> 00:21:10,810
Raise the bed for me.

336
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,570
Okay, raise the bed.

337
00:21:13,971 --> 00:21:14,931
The opposite way.

338
00:21:14,931 --> 00:21:15,770
Opposite way.

339
00:21:15,931 --> 00:21:17,851
Got it. It's working now.

340
00:21:21,050 --> 00:21:21,611
Is that okay?

341
00:21:22,330 --> 00:21:23,570
Keep your voice down.

342
00:21:32,290 --> 00:21:34,770
The water is cold.
I'll pour it out here first.

343
00:21:41,451 --> 00:21:43,171
It's warm. Have a sip.

344
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:46,570
What's wrong?

345
00:21:48,411 --> 00:21:49,131
Slowly.

346
00:21:50,290 --> 00:21:51,810
I brought you spicy pepper beef.

347
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:53,651
You were saving it, remember?

348
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,250
Here, it's all yours.

349
00:21:55,810 --> 00:21:57,221
Try it. It's still warm.

350
00:21:57,221 --> 00:21:58,290
You're sitting on my hand.

351
00:21:58,611 --> 00:21:59,570
My hand.

352
00:22:00,730 --> 00:22:02,290
Have some stir-fried spicy pepper...

353
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:03,330
Spicy pepper beef!

354
00:22:06,371 --> 00:22:06,931
Mom.

355
00:22:07,691 --> 00:22:08,611
Hello, ma'am.

356
00:22:08,971 --> 00:22:10,810
She has acute intestinal volvulus.

357
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:13,530
Intestinal perforation.
And you're feeding her this?

358
00:23:24,691 --> 00:23:25,451
Stop staring.

359
00:23:28,931 --> 00:23:29,730
Why are you crying?

360
00:23:31,050 --> 00:23:32,250
You feel wronged?

361
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:38,451
I didn't ask you to come.

362
00:23:39,651 --> 00:23:41,290
You cause trouble for me all the time.

363
00:23:41,611 --> 00:23:43,451
I traveled overnight on a hard seat.

364
00:23:43,451 --> 00:23:45,451
I didn't make you do that.
Serves you right.

365
00:23:45,770 --> 00:23:46,290
Serves...

366
00:23:50,770 --> 00:23:51,651
Serves me right.

367
00:23:52,211 --> 00:23:53,211
Eat this and die.

368
00:23:53,330 --> 00:23:54,330
Fine, I'll die.

369
00:23:59,171 --> 00:24:00,570
Ma'am, pinch me instead.

370
00:24:00,570 --> 00:24:02,050
Don't pinch her. She's still sick.

371
00:24:02,290 --> 00:24:04,490
- It's your fault.
- It hurts!

372
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:05,810
You dragged her down.

373
00:24:06,050 --> 00:24:07,131
If you hadn't come,

374
00:24:07,131 --> 00:24:09,411
would she be in this terrible state?

375
00:24:10,530 --> 00:24:13,290
Why are you scolding him?
What does it have to do with him?

376
00:24:14,131 --> 00:24:15,891
Don't pinch her. Don't.

377
00:24:15,891 --> 00:24:18,131
Don't pinch her. Pinch me. Hit me.

378
00:24:19,131 --> 00:24:19,971
I...

379
00:24:32,330 --> 00:24:33,010
Bottoms up.

380
00:24:33,010 --> 00:24:33,611
Come on.

381
00:25:32,211 --> 00:25:32,891
Mom.

382
00:25:33,050 --> 00:25:34,131
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

383
00:25:34,211 --> 00:25:35,090
Mom.

384
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:37,010
Mom.

385
00:25:37,530 --> 00:25:39,090
Mom, don't just stay silent.

386
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:41,971
Mom.

387
00:25:43,050 --> 00:25:44,490
What are you doing?

388
00:25:45,451 --> 00:25:47,810
What are you doing? Say something.

389
00:25:47,810 --> 00:25:49,651
Don't just stay silent, Mom.

390
00:25:55,131 --> 00:25:55,931
Mom.

391
00:26:26,691 --> 00:26:29,211
(After she found out
I was with He Yuqiong,)

392
00:26:29,810 --> 00:26:31,171
(she wouldn't answer my calls.)

393
00:26:34,211 --> 00:26:37,250
The subscriber you dialed is busy.

394
00:26:37,530 --> 00:26:38,810
Please try again later.

395
00:26:38,810 --> 00:26:40,730
Sorry, the subscriber you dialed...

396
00:26:45,050 --> 00:26:47,891
Sorry, the subscriber you dialed
is powered off.

397
00:26:48,090 --> 00:26:52,090
Sorry, the subscriber you dialed
is powered off.

398
00:26:58,971 --> 00:27:01,250
(The relationship they forbade
by yelling and hitting)

399
00:27:01,570 --> 00:27:02,931
(feels great.)

400
00:27:03,971 --> 00:27:04,891
(But things change)

401
00:27:05,810 --> 00:27:07,010
(once no one is watching.)

402
00:27:27,411 --> 00:27:28,651
You didn't take out the trash?

403
00:27:30,010 --> 00:27:31,290
I just got back.

404
00:27:33,691 --> 00:27:34,851
It's so hot.

405
00:27:35,730 --> 00:27:37,131
It stinks. Don't you smell it?

406
00:27:37,810 --> 00:27:39,171
You smell it too, don't you?

407
00:27:45,171 --> 00:27:46,371
I'll take them out later.

408
00:28:35,971 --> 00:28:37,371
Can you keep it down?

409
00:28:50,891 --> 00:28:51,691
I fell asleep.

410
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:52,611
Can you be quiet? I'm studying here.

411
00:29:52,611 --> 00:29:54,330
How can I study like this?

412
00:29:55,891 --> 00:29:57,931
I have an exam tomorrow.

413
00:30:31,891 --> 00:30:33,611
I'm taking these clothes back.

414
00:30:34,810 --> 00:30:36,290
They don't get any sun here.

415
00:30:37,371 --> 00:30:38,570
Autumn clothes are thick.

416
00:30:39,651 --> 00:30:40,411
Too damp here.

417
00:30:41,851 --> 00:30:42,490
They smell.

418
00:30:43,691 --> 00:30:44,691
Of what?

419
00:30:47,931 --> 00:30:48,770
Mold.

420
00:31:02,371 --> 00:31:03,330
They do smell.

421
00:31:04,810 --> 00:31:07,171
Go back to the dorm. It's better there.

422
00:31:31,851 --> 00:31:34,730
Come on,
cheers to finishing the last exam.

423
00:31:35,131 --> 00:31:35,770
Cheers.

424
00:31:43,010 --> 00:31:45,010
Your mom still doesn't answer?

425
00:31:48,451 --> 00:31:49,931
I understand her really well.

426
00:31:50,330 --> 00:31:52,131
I wouldn't answer your calls, either.

427
00:31:53,611 --> 00:31:55,530
Why did you kick me?

428
00:31:57,090 --> 00:31:58,490
Xiaoming got into the university.

429
00:31:58,490 --> 00:32:01,010
She and her boyfriend
are heading down different paths.

430
00:32:02,010 --> 00:32:04,810
Why force them down the same path?

431
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:06,730
You're way too realistic.

432
00:32:06,971 --> 00:32:09,050
She should dump him
because she got into university?

433
00:32:09,851 --> 00:32:11,371
It's not about the university.

434
00:32:12,611 --> 00:32:15,490
It's about the gap. The gap in life.

435
00:32:16,250 --> 00:32:17,290
What gap?

436
00:32:17,691 --> 00:32:18,971
You're just being snobbish.

437
00:32:19,530 --> 00:32:21,810
There are differences, but not a gap.

438
00:32:22,490 --> 00:32:25,090
Don't act like saintly little angels.

439
00:32:25,330 --> 00:32:27,171
Avoiding the problem
is creating a problem.

440
00:32:27,651 --> 00:32:29,290
I mean well for her boyfriend too.

441
00:32:29,490 --> 00:32:30,770
Think about it.

442
00:32:31,131 --> 00:32:33,090
Xiaoming came here to study.

443
00:32:33,451 --> 00:32:34,490
That's her life.

444
00:32:35,090 --> 00:32:38,411
What about him? He left his hometown.

445
00:32:38,691 --> 00:32:40,411
He came entirely for Xiaoming.

446
00:32:40,691 --> 00:32:43,250
Does he really want to
have a life in Qingzhou?

447
00:32:43,490 --> 00:32:44,931
Does he want to live here?

448
00:32:45,371 --> 00:32:48,371
No friends, no connections.
He has to start over.

449
00:32:48,810 --> 00:32:49,851
Isn't it exhausting?

450
00:33:07,826 --> 00:33:12,146
(Qidaohezi Railway Station)

451
00:33:34,530 --> 00:33:35,330
You got this?

452
00:33:36,090 --> 00:33:36,810
I got this.

453
00:33:37,691 --> 00:33:39,451
I'll walk you home first.

454
00:33:41,211 --> 00:33:41,931
No need.

455
00:33:42,730 --> 00:33:45,891
Are you still mad that I quit my job?

456
00:33:47,490 --> 00:33:51,770
I can find work.
I'm not there to make money.

457
00:33:51,851 --> 00:33:53,411
Being with you comes first.

458
00:33:59,050 --> 00:34:00,211
Do you like Qingzhou?

459
00:34:03,371 --> 00:34:04,371
I wouldn't say I like it.

460
00:34:04,371 --> 00:34:05,570
So you don't like it.

461
00:34:08,050 --> 00:34:09,891
Then stay after the new year.

462
00:34:10,291 --> 00:34:13,371
Don't worry. I'll definitely find a job.

463
00:34:13,851 --> 00:34:17,050
I'm going to Qingzhou for school.
Why are you going there?

464
00:34:18,010 --> 00:34:19,570
To be a rat in someone's basement?

465
00:34:20,490 --> 00:34:21,771
Or to do heavy labor?

466
00:34:27,411 --> 00:34:28,331
That's unnecessary.

467
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:31,050
I know you feel sorry for me.

468
00:34:31,170 --> 00:34:34,331
But I'm tough. I can handle any job.

469
00:34:34,411 --> 00:34:36,010
I'm happy being with you.

470
00:34:37,130 --> 00:34:40,530
Isn't it nice here?
You have your family and friends.

471
00:34:40,971 --> 00:34:42,610
Why do you have to follow me?

472
00:34:43,411 --> 00:34:45,690
Why do you think I have to follow you?

473
00:34:48,371 --> 00:34:49,570
Because I'm outstanding.

474
00:34:51,851 --> 00:34:53,210
Feeling confident now?

475
00:34:54,451 --> 00:34:55,731
Yeah, you're the best.

476
00:34:56,251 --> 00:34:58,130
So I'll go further and further.

477
00:34:58,771 --> 00:35:00,451
Will you be able to keep up?

478
00:35:01,130 --> 00:35:02,210
I'll try my best.

479
00:35:02,570 --> 00:35:06,210
But even if I fail,
I believe you'll come back one day.

480
00:35:06,490 --> 00:35:08,530
I'll build a home for you here.

481
00:35:09,010 --> 00:35:10,451
What if I don't come back?

482
00:35:12,130 --> 00:35:14,130
Cut it out. You couldn't bear it.

483
00:35:14,411 --> 00:35:17,610
You said that you're just
one in twenty million out there.

484
00:35:17,811 --> 00:35:19,891
Here we have our family, friends,
and classmates.

485
00:35:20,331 --> 00:35:22,251
Don't you always crave the local food?

486
00:35:22,690 --> 00:35:24,251
Someone shouts in her sleep,

487
00:35:24,411 --> 00:35:26,610
"I want Guo Bao Rou!"

488
00:35:26,731 --> 00:35:28,130
- "I..."
- He Yuqiong.

489
00:35:29,331 --> 00:35:31,251
For me, home is something
to be remembered.

490
00:35:32,530 --> 00:35:34,170
I worked so hard

491
00:35:35,251 --> 00:35:36,650
to get into Qingzhou University,

492
00:35:36,650 --> 00:35:39,210
not just to study there for four years.

493
00:35:54,090 --> 00:35:55,251
I'll definitely find a job.

494
00:35:55,251 --> 00:35:56,731
Don't follow me.

495
00:36:35,331 --> 00:36:38,210
You bought such a huge TV, Xiaoming?

496
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:39,610
That's so nice.

497
00:36:46,811 --> 00:36:47,771
Xiaoming, you're back.

498
00:36:57,371 --> 00:36:58,530
Xiaoming, you're back.

499
00:37:12,451 --> 00:37:13,690
Xiaoming, you're back.

500
00:37:14,291 --> 00:37:15,851
You bought such a big TV?

501
00:37:24,690 --> 00:37:27,570
Xiaofei, open the door.

502
00:37:28,291 --> 00:37:30,010
Mom, Xiaoming is back.

503
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:33,771
Xiaofei.

504
00:37:34,731 --> 00:37:35,851
Open up, Ren Xiaofei.

505
00:37:35,851 --> 00:37:37,931
Mom, let her in.

506
00:37:39,891 --> 00:37:41,851
Ren Xiaofei, open the door.

507
00:37:41,851 --> 00:37:44,210
Mom, please.

508
00:37:47,371 --> 00:37:48,090
Mom.

509
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:49,731
Mom, please.

510
00:37:50,170 --> 00:37:51,371
Let her in.

511
00:37:52,010 --> 00:37:53,170
Let her in.

512
00:37:53,331 --> 00:37:54,210
Mom.

513
00:37:57,731 --> 00:37:59,411
No one opens that door today.

514
00:37:59,411 --> 00:38:00,130
Xiaofei.

515
00:38:02,130 --> 00:38:02,650
Mom.

516
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:06,010
Xiaoming.

517
00:38:06,690 --> 00:38:07,530
Xiaoming.

518
00:38:07,530 --> 00:38:08,971
If you open that door today,

519
00:38:08,971 --> 00:38:10,530
I will lock her up in here.

520
00:38:10,530 --> 00:38:11,891
She hasn't graduated yet.

521
00:38:11,891 --> 00:38:14,291
You want her
to finish her education, don't you?

522
00:38:14,331 --> 00:38:15,010
Mom.

523
00:38:16,130 --> 00:38:17,170
Ren Xiaoming.

524
00:38:17,771 --> 00:38:19,331
Xiaoming.

525
00:38:19,851 --> 00:38:20,490
Xiaoming.

526
00:38:20,851 --> 00:38:21,570
- Xiaoming.
- Mom.

527
00:38:23,170 --> 00:38:23,690
Xiaoming.

528
00:38:24,851 --> 00:38:25,490
Xiaoming.

529
00:38:26,291 --> 00:38:26,851
Xiaoming.

530
00:38:27,291 --> 00:38:27,851
Xiaoming.

531
00:38:27,931 --> 00:38:28,530
Mom.

532
00:38:31,010 --> 00:38:32,811
Stop shouting, Ren Xiaofei.

533
00:38:32,811 --> 00:38:33,931
She can't follow my path.

534
00:38:33,931 --> 00:38:34,650
Mom.

535
00:38:34,891 --> 00:38:36,050
Mom.

536
00:38:36,050 --> 00:38:36,570
Xiaoming.

537
00:38:36,570 --> 00:38:40,971
I ran away from home
and ended up like this.

538
00:38:42,610 --> 00:38:44,210
Don't be like me.

539
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:45,570
Xiaoming.

540
00:38:46,371 --> 00:38:46,931
Xiaoming.

541
00:38:46,931 --> 00:38:48,690
- She can't walk down my old path.
- Mom.

542
00:38:48,690 --> 00:38:51,490
If I let her in,
I would be ruining her life.

543
00:38:52,130 --> 00:38:53,690
- Xiaoming.
- Get inside.

544
00:38:55,010 --> 00:38:58,130
Ren Xiaoming,
you're going to be an educated person.

545
00:38:58,490 --> 00:39:00,090
You can't marry a street vendor.

546
00:39:01,411 --> 00:39:03,931
You and He Yuqiong
will live in different worlds.

547
00:39:04,451 --> 00:39:07,530
Mark my words. We'll see.

548
00:39:07,530 --> 00:39:08,451
Mom.

549
00:39:09,170 --> 00:39:11,010
- I know you care about us.
- Mom.

550
00:39:11,291 --> 00:39:12,530
If you don't break up with him,

551
00:39:12,891 --> 00:39:14,731
you'll never set foot
in this house again.

552
00:39:16,731 --> 00:39:17,650
Mom.

553
00:39:34,731 --> 00:39:35,690
Ren Meiyan.

554
00:39:37,490 --> 00:39:39,170
You two enjoy your New Year.

555
00:39:44,610 --> 00:39:45,971
I left the TV by the door.

556
00:40:28,754 --> 00:40:31,602
(2023, Qingzhou)

557
00:40:32,771 --> 00:40:34,771
Was I wrong back then?

558
00:40:35,291 --> 00:40:37,368
If I had let Xiaoming come home

559
00:40:37,901 --> 00:40:39,210
and let them be together,

560
00:40:39,690 --> 00:40:43,570
would she be feeling better right now?

561
00:40:46,251 --> 00:40:48,291
Ma'am, it's all in the past.

562
00:40:50,971 --> 00:40:52,891
There are too many regrets.

563
00:40:54,090 --> 00:40:55,170
If only I'd known...

564
00:40:58,331 --> 00:40:59,010
People

565
00:40:59,251 --> 00:41:01,811
always suffer from the idea
"if only I'd known".

566
00:41:04,210 --> 00:41:07,331
Even if we had known
and chosen a different path,

567
00:41:07,570 --> 00:41:08,891
it might not have been right.

568
00:41:09,771 --> 00:41:11,650
It's just that we can't verify it.

569
00:41:12,411 --> 00:41:13,851
That's why it seems better.

570
00:41:18,090 --> 00:41:21,690
Bai Shu, I want to
visit Xiaoming in Qingzhou.

571
00:41:22,050 --> 00:41:25,690
While I'm away,
could you help look after Xiaofei?

572
00:41:26,251 --> 00:41:27,690
Sure, no problem.

573
00:41:29,851 --> 00:41:31,371
I used to say

574
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:34,411
that Xiaoming would be the last person
to have a mental illness.

575
00:41:35,010 --> 00:41:38,690
I said she was selfish and would never
put herself through hardship.

576
00:41:40,570 --> 00:41:42,130
But lately, I've been thinking

577
00:41:43,610 --> 00:41:45,371
that she's really hard on herself.

578
00:41:46,811 --> 00:41:48,251
She always talks back to me,

579
00:41:50,170 --> 00:41:52,050
but deep down she's very sweet.

580
00:41:52,731 --> 00:41:55,851
Since she was little,
she's been taking care of her brother

581
00:41:58,971 --> 00:42:01,130
and saving up for the family.

582
00:42:07,371 --> 00:42:11,490
My daughter is actually
very good and very sweet.

583
00:42:12,771 --> 00:42:14,090
It's all my fault.

584
00:42:15,050 --> 00:42:17,771
I never gave her a stable home.

585
00:42:22,530 --> 00:42:25,731
It's just a pity
that I realized this a bit too late.

586
00:42:28,411 --> 00:42:31,090
Ms. Ren, don't dwell on it.

587
00:42:38,866 --> 00:42:40,838
(Ren Xiaoming)

588
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
